	            </svg>	                    <img src="https://www.contemporaryceramics.uk/wp-content/plugins/instagram-feed/img/placeholder.png" alt="Carolyn Genders, Colour and Form in Dialogue - Now open online and at Ceramics Africa 

In our newest exhibition, Colour and Form in Dialogue, Carolyn Genders uses colour and gestural spontaneity to explore relations between form and surface. Her thin-walled vessels are seen as an expression of emotion occupying a space, not just a ‘feeling’ or a ‘memory’. 

Carolyn Genders was born in Singapore and now lives and works on the South coast of England. Carolyn is an internationally respected ceramic artist acknowledged for her asymmetric sculptural vessels and forms and her unique use of colour and surface. 

Works are on display in the gallery and online from now until Saturday 7th October 2023. 

Follow the link in bio to shop the exhibition.
