            <span class="sbi-screenreader">‘Collaborating with Stephen has rekindled my ori</span>
            <svg class="svg-inline--fa fa-clone fa-w-16 sbi_lightbox_carousel_icon" aria-hidden="true" aria-label="Clone" data-fa-proƒcessed="" data-prefix="far" data-icon="clone" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
	                <path fill="currentColor" d="M464 0H144c-26.51 0-48 21.49-48 48v48H48c-26.51 0-48 21.49-48 48v320c0 26.51 21.49 48 48 48h320c26.51 0 48-21.49 48-48v-48h48c26.51 0 48-21.49 48-48V48c0-26.51-21.49-48-48-48zM362 464H54a6 6 0 0 1-6-6V150a6 6 0 0 1 6-6h42v224c0 26.51 21.49 48 48 48h224v42a6 6 0 0 1-6 6zm96-96H150a6 6 0 0 1-6-6V54a6 6 0 0 1 6-6h308a6 6 0 0 1 6 6v308a6 6 0 0 1-6 6z"></path>
	            </svg>	                    <img src="https://www.contemporaryceramics.uk/wp-content/plugins/instagram-feed/img/placeholder.png" alt="‘Collaborating with Stephen has rekindled my original love of the simple beauty of fire and glaze,while at the same time continue to experiment with storytelling 
through print and drawing. My focus has been to see how these two very different approaches can be used to draw attention to the beauty and fragility of nature.’ @loneborgen 

Through a collaborative process, Stephen Parry and Lone Borgen explore what happens when the thick slips and wood ash of Parry&#039;s thrown wood fired pots meet the prints, drawings and lustre firing of Borgen&#039;s highly decorated hand-built work.

Stephen Parry and Lone Borgen are participating in our newest exhibition, Moonlight, which celebrates the ubiquitous form of the Korean moon jar and how ceramic artists have adopted and personalised this most iconic jar.

With Matthew Blakely @atdbuick @adamfrewceramics @jaejunlee_ceramics @stephenparryceramics and Tricia Thom

Follow the link in bio to shop the exhibition

17th August - 9th September 2023">
